well actually I'd say Fate/Stay Night breaks the shackles of a simple "eroge" to become a masterclass in high art.

Not only does the VN have a compelling story, memorable soundtrack, and anime titties but it also has a theme. you know what that theme is? that's right, the human condition.

Some might say that the second ero scene in the fate route is "unnecessary" and "shoehorned" but that's just the genius himself, Nasu, Subverting the expectations of the reader and putting them in an 'anything can happen' mindset. You pathetic onlookers only see the surface-level value of these scenes, eye candy, you cannot see their masterfully-executed yet intentionally-mistransmitted messages on acceptance and the value of human life.

You can choke your chicken all you want, but I will be bathing in the symbolism.
